WHO   — NINTENDO WII — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Nintendo skipped the HD arms race and won the generation on a different axis: motion control. Modest, efficient PowerPC silicon — essentially an overclocked GameCube — drove a runaway hit because the magic was in the Wii Remote's sensors, not the teraflops.
